<br>
You can view a full explination of what I've learned through the process on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqinterface.com/forums/showthread.php?s=78c72b93ba7c28a6b867ddd346a59a63&amp;threadid=1451">my post</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> at the EQGUI Forums.<br>
<br>
Now, for the PlayerWindow I've created:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><center>  <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.gpcentre.net/images/evercrack/gui/fullplayerwindow.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></center><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
It's a set of 6 Windows in one main window. Total of 8 files in the archive for this; 6 custom window files, the EQUI_PlayerWindow.xml and a ReadMe.html file.<br>
<br>
The archive and a preview of what it looks like it game can be located in the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.gpcentre.net/evercrack/gui/player-pet.html">Player/Pet Window</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> section of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.gpcentre.net/">my website</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
Each window can also be turned on and off with ease. This isn't in the ReadMe yet, but it's only in beta. Any UI coder can figure it out w/out any trouble. I plan to clean up more things and maybe add more things to it in the future.<br>
<br>
PS: Here's a pict with all the Borders turned on, so you can see the placements: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.gpcentre.net/images/evercrack/gui/fullplayerwindow-borders.gif">Borders On</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Ignore the missplaced PetHP bar. Turning borders on shifts the elements a wee bit.<br>
<br>
